main event: A mysterious object, described as an elliptic cylinder approximately 30 feet long, was sighted over Crestone, Colorado on multiple occasions between August 22-30, 1956.
interesting points: The object appeared to be stationary and was observed for up to 1 hour and 30 minutes at a time.
The object was sighted on three separate occasions during this time period.
The sightings were made both visually and by ground radar.
The report indicates that there was insufficient data to evaluate the nature of the object.
The sightings occurred over a rural area in Colorado.
sighted object: An elliptic cylinder-shaped object, approximately 30 feet long
